{"TopicId":158007,"ForumId":32,"TopicTitle":"Rocket Assisted Take-Off Fans?","CreatedByName":"Alpha 360","CreatedById":166007,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-21T09:02:34Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Alpha 360","CreatedById":166007,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-21T09:02:34Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have always enjoyed using solid rocket boosters strapped to the wings of a \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003ESSTO\u003C/abbr\u003E, just to give it a booster on the way up as well as giving it the most awesome look I have ever seen, any buyers?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-03-21T09:02:51Z\u0022 title=\u002203/21/2017 09:02  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 21, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by Alpha 360\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\u0026quot;Kouston, we have several problems, but that doesn\u0026#039;t matter so we want to continue on with the mission.\u0026quot;\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"p1t1o","CreatedById":74091,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-21T09:38:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAt first I was like \u0022Rocket-assisted-fan?\u00A0how is that supposed to work?!\u0022\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut yeah, I like me few ginormous RATO boosters \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"TheKosanianMethod","CreatedById":163034,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-21T11:10:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI had an \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003ESSTO\u003C/abbr\u003E that used four jets. It would get to space pretty quickly. But not fast enough for me. I threw two \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Solid fuel Rocket Booster\u0022\u003ESRB\u003C/abbr\u003E\u0027s on. Mach one by the end of the runway.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Alpha 360","CreatedById":166007,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-21T11:28:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSame here, same here. Any tips on mounting them without them exploding anything important? I just slap them on the wings with the largest, tallest decouplers (don\u0027t know any other way off putting it). Also, do you prefer kickbacks or BACC Thumpers?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-03-21T11:28:51Z\u0022 title=\u002203/21/2017 11:28  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 21, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by Alpha 360\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\u0026quot;Kouston, we have several problems, but that doesn\u0026#039;t matter so we want to continue on with the mission.\u0026quot;\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Alpha 360","CreatedById":166007,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-21T14:35:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHere is a picture of my RATO \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003ESSTO\u003C/abbr\u003E\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022http://imgur.com/bIYjfD8\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://imgur.com/bIYjfD8\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-03-21T14:35:20Z\u0022 title=\u002203/21/2017 02:35  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 21, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by Alpha 360\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\u0026quot;Kouston, we have several problems, but that doesn\u0026#039;t matter so we want to continue on with the mission.\u0026quot;\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Foxster","CreatedById":113764,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-21T16:16:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis kind of thing\u00A0works well...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022k7xxLr0.png?1\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/k7xxLr0.png?1\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-03-21T16:31:34Z\u0022 title=\u002203/21/2017 04:31  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 21, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by Foxster\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DoctorDavinci","CreatedById":150019,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-21T16:23:50Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222992592\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022158007\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221490095724\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022166007\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Alpha 360\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, Alpha 360 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAny tips on mounting them without them exploding anything important?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nUse Structural Pylons instead of decouplers ... look nicer and they are much better at not causing a \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Rapid unplanned disassembly\u0022\u003ERUD\u003C/abbr\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Rapid unplanned disassembly\u0022\u003EThey work the same as a decoupler\u003C/abbr\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-03-21T16:25:27Z\u0022 title=\u002203/21/2017 04:25  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 21, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by DoctorDavinci\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"CaptainTrebor","CreatedById":172975,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-21T21:13:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have a RATO aircraft because it\u0027s Juno engines are too weak for a short take off. Also it is fun.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gargamel","CreatedById":64714,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-21T21:48:34Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222992523\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022158007\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221490089105\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002274091\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022p1t1o\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n12 hours ago, p1t1o said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAt first I was like \u0022Rocket-assisted-fan?\u00A0how is that supposed to work?!\u0022\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut yeah, I like me few ginormous RATO boosters \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWouldn\u0027t that be how Iron man saved the heli-carrier?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd on a side note.... these are not SSTOs any more, just regular spaceplanes.\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0 \u0026lt;/pendant\u0026gt;\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"p1t1o","CreatedById":74091,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-22T09:34:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222993059\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022158007\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221490132914\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002264714\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022gargamel\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n11 hours ago, gargamel said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWouldn\u0027t that be how Iron man saved the heli-carrier?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd on a side note.... these are not SSTOs any more, just regular spaceplanes.\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0 \u0026lt;/pendant\u0026gt;\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot \u0022stage-and-a-half\u0022?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHow many \u0022stages\u0022 was the space shuttle stack?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:11px;\u0022\u003E...its pedant \u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:11px;\u0022\u003E/pedant\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kBob","CreatedById":102132,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-22T11:26:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ll admit to doing this from time to time though it\u0027s usually just fleas to give a quick boost, but those bigger ones are a temptation.\u00A0 Also I\u0027m cheap and SRBs fit that mentality quite well.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gargamel","CreatedById":64714,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-23T07:58:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222993484\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022158007\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221490175249\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002274091\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022p1t1o\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n22 hours ago, p1t1o said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHow many \u0022stages\u0022 was the space shuttle stack?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:11px;\u0022\u003E...its pedant \u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:11px;\u0022\u003E/pedant\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n3 I think.\u00A0 Boosters, main Engines, and then OMS.\u00A0 Argument could be made for 2.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI knew pendant didn\u0027t seem right.\u00A0 Thanks.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"MinimalMinmus","CreatedById":172387,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-23T09:23:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI do this even for small planes, when I have trouble making them take off: I simply strap a pair of sepratrons or (SpaceY) ejectatrons, and suddenly it takes off with 1/4 of the runway available.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Alpha 360","CreatedById":166007,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-23T13:35:49Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNothing beats attaching solid rocket boosters(the most KERBAL boosters) to a \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003ESSTO\u003C/abbr\u003E, (which is the most KERBAL plane) to exceed supersonic speeds(which also very KERBAL), to go to space (which is the most kerbal of all of the above)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBasically, RATO SSTOs is\u00A0the most kerbal you can get\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:cool:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cool.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:cool:\u0022\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-03-23T13:35:57Z\u0022 title=\u002203/23/2017 01:35  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 23, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by Alpha 360\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\u0026quot;Kouston, we have several problems, but that doesn\u0026#039;t matter so we want to continue on with the mission.\u0026quot;\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"mattinoz","CreatedById":118580,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-24T01:16:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222993059\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022158007\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221490132914\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002264714\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022gargamel\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 22/03/2017 at 8:48 AM, gargamel said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWouldn\u0027t that be how Iron man saved the heli-carrier?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd on a side note.... these are not SSTOs any more, just regular spaceplanes.\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0 \u0026lt;/pendant\u0026gt;\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Cdiv title=\u0022Protected by Grammarly\u0022\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat if you eject boosters before leaving the ground? Would that still be a \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003ESSTO\u003C/abbr\u003E?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNow to find a catapult runway mod.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Rath","CreatedById":138223,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-24T03:12:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222995459\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022158007\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221490318200\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022118580\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022mattinoz\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, mattinoz said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat if you eject boosters before leaving the ground? Would that still be a \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003ESSTO\u003C/abbr\u003E?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNow to find a catapult runway mod.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere\u0027s a mod with an aircraft carrier deck, it made a catapult system by having a gap (usually stowed but the deck was animated so it could open) that the front landing gear fit in. \u00A0It had a block in the back that pushed the gear forward to accelerate the plane.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI don\u0027t remember what it was called.\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:(\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_sad.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:(\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gargamel","CreatedById":64714,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-24T05:59:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222995459\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022158007\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221490318200\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022118580\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022mattinoz\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, mattinoz said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat if you eject boosters before leaving the ground? Would that still be a \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003ESSTO\u003C/abbr\u003E?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNow to find a catapult runway mod.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003ESSTO\u003C/abbr\u003E stands for Single Stage to Orbit.\u00A0 Any type of staging is,unsurprisingly, a multiple stage vehicle.\u00A0 \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003ESSTO\u003C/abbr\u003E does not mean space plane.\u00A0 You can make a \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003ESSTO\u003C/abbr\u003E vertical launch rocket.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"dci","CreatedById":106864,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-24T16:14:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have one for \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Low Kerbin Orbit\u0022\u003ELKO\u003C/abbr\u003E rescue missions. Small spaceplane with two expendable BACC-10 boosters and one aerospike. \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Delta-V\u0022\u003EdV\u003C/abbr\u003E is about 3700m/s, more than I need for such missions.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTechnically, it is not pure \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003ESSTO\u003C/abbr\u003E as I decouple boosters. But then, Atlas V with boosters should be 3 stage rocket, not two as introduced everywhere.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"nascarlaser1","CreatedById":166190,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-24T16:43:34Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222992582\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022158007\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221490094629\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022163034\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022TheKosanianMethod\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn \u200E3\u200E/\u200E21\u200E/\u200E2017 at 7:10 AM, TheKosanianMethod said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI had an \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003ESSTO\u003C/abbr\u003E that used four jets. It would get to space pretty quickly. But not fast enough for me. I threw two \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Solid fuel Rocket Booster\u0022\u003ESRB\u003C/abbr\u003E\u0027s on. Mach one by the end of the runway.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have a plane that uses just vector engines and hits mach 2 before leaving runway and mach 4 shortly after \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-03-24T16:44:40Z\u0022 title=\u002203/24/2017 04:44  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 24, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by nascarlaser1\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"A_name","CreatedById":134040,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-25T00:31:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222994512\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022158007\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221490255921\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002264714\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022gargamel\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 23/3/2017 at 1:58 AM, gargamel said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n3 I think.\u00A0 Boosters, main Engines, and then OMS.\u00A0 Argument could be made for 2.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI knew pendant didn\u0027t seem right.\u00A0 Thanks.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell you would have to hit spacebar 3 times, so I would say it\u0027s 3.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Overland","CreatedById":119812,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-25T07:28:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat about the other way?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot so much planes exclusively but ive been known to put an array of forward firing seperons on craft to function as an emergency air brake both in aviation and railway terms.. Its rather useful thing\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlthough we do have drag chutes now for this..it seems less...kerbal\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNothing beats hitting abort key and having brilliant blinding flames shoot out over the locomotives nose as a last resort\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSame for aircraft that landed too hot\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAs long as you dont be all C130 and fire them in the air..at which point the air deems you unworthy and vacates airfoils, control surfaces and its friend the ground welcomes you with open arms\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}